{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867132995,"sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","part":{"id":"prt_d79edfc07001pbn4kjLOjGDS6y","messageID":"msg_d79ede6f1001AoyYf2GUcODcCA","sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fd56200b0eb240fcb88085243dc0a561","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: 实现 AgentCube CLI 的 `build` 命令，用于从打包好的工作空间构建容器镜像。该命令支持本地 Docker 构建和云端构建两种模式，能够自动管理版本号、验证构建前置条件，并集成 Docker 服务进行镜像构建。\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 提供 `kubectl-agentcube build` 命令，实现：\n10: \n11: 1. **本地 Docker 构建**：使用本地 Docker 守护进程构建容器镜像\n12: 2. **云端构建**：集成云服务商（如华为云）的构建服务\n13: 3. **版本管理**：自动递增版本号（patch 级别），构建失败时回滚版本\n14: 4. **代理支持**：支持自定义代理 URL 进行依赖解析\n15: 5. **构建结果输出**：输出镜像名称、ID、大小等构建信息\n16: 6. **元数据更新**：更新 `agent_metadata.yaml` 中的构建信息\n17: \n18: ## Module\n19: \n20: `cmd/cli` - AgentCube CLI 工具包\n21: \n22: ## Language\n23: \n24: Python 3.10+\n25: \n26: ## Size\n27: \n28: M\n29: \n30: ## Scope\n31: \n32: ### In Scope\n33: \n34: 1. **BuildRuntime 类实现** (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n35:    - `build()` 主方法，支持本地和云端构建模式\n36:    - `_increment_version()` - 版本号递增逻辑\n37:    - `_validate_build_prerequisites()` - 构建前置条件验证\n38:    - `_build_local()` - 本地 Docker 构建\n39:    - `_build_cloud()` - 云端构建（华为云等）\n40:    - `_update_build_metadata()` - 更新构建元数据\n41: \n42: 2. **CLI 命令集成** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n43:    - `build()` Typer 命令函数\n44:    - 命令行参数：`--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n45:    - 错误处理和用户反馈\n46: \n47: 3. **Docker 服务集成** (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n48:    - `build_image()` - 构建镜像方法\n49:    - 支持构建参数（buildargs）\n50:    - 支持代理配置\n51:    - 返回镜像信息（名称、ID、大小、构建时间）\n52: \n53: 4. **元数据服务集成** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n54:    - 加载和保存 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n55:    - 版本管理\n56:    - 构建结果持久化\n57: \n58: ### Out of Scope\n59: \n60: - Docker 守护进程安装和配置\n61: - 云服务提供商 SDK 实现（使用已有 SDK）\n62: - Dockerfile 生成（由 `pack` 命令完成）\n63: - 镜像推送功能（由 `publish` 命令完成）\n64: \n65: ## Impact Analysis\n66: \n67: ### Components Impacted\n68: \n69: 1. **CLI 工具包** (`cmd/cli`)\n70:    - 添加 `build` 命令到 Typer 应用\n71:    - 新增 `BuildRuntime` 类\n72:    - 更新导入和依赖\n73: \n74: 2. **Docker 服务** (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n75:    - 确保已实现 `build_image()` 方法\n76:    - 支持代理配置\n77:    - 支持构建参数传递\n78: \n79: 3. **元数据服务** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n80:    - 需要支持版本更新\n81:    - 需要支持构建信息存储\n82: \n83: 4. **用户工作流**\n84:    - `pack` → `build` → `publish` 的完整链路\n85:    - 元数据文件在命令间传递状态\n86: \n87: ### Dependencies\n88: \n89: **核心依赖**（已在 `pyproject.toml` 中定义）：\n90: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI 框架\n91: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - 数据验证\n92: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML 解析\n93: - `docker>=6.0.0` - Docker SDK\n94: - `rich>=13.0.0` - 美化输出\n95: - `semver>=3.0.0` - 语义化版本管理\n96: \n97: **可选依赖**：\n98: - `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP 客户端（云端构建）\n99: \n100: ### Security Considerations\n101: \n102: 1. **Docker 守护进程访问**\n103:    - 验证 Docker 守护进程是否可访问\n104:    - 检查 Docker 权限\n105:    - 避免构建敏感信息泄露到镜像\n106: \n107: 2. **代理安全**\n108:    - 支持安全的代理 URL（HTTPS）\n109:    - 避免在日志中输出代理凭证\n110:    - 支持代理认证（环境变量）\n111: \n112: 3. **元数据安全**\n113:    - 避免在元数据中存储敏感信息\n114:    - 版本号递增时的原子性\n115:    - 构建失败时的回滚机制\n116: \n117: 4. **云构建安全**\n118:    - 支持云服务认证凭证\n119:    - 避免在日志中输出凭证\n120:    - 支持凭证轮换\n121: \n122: ## Design Decisions\n123: \n124: ### 构建模式选择\n125: \n126: **选择**：支持本地和云端两种构建模式\n127: \n128: **理由**：\n129: - 本地构建：开发、测试、小规模部署\n130: - 云端构建：生产环境、大规模部署、CI/CD\n131: - 满足不同用户需求\n132: \n133: **实现**：\n134: ```python\n135: if build_mode == \"local\":\n136:     return self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n137: elif build_mode == \"cloud\":\n138:     return self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n139: else:\n140:     raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {build_mode}\")\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ### 版本管理策略\n144: \n145: **选择**：自动递增 patch 版本，构建失败时回滚\n146: \n147: **理由**：\n148: - 自动版本号管理减少用户负担\n149: - 构建失败时保持版本一致性\n150: - 符合语义化版本规范\n151: \n152: **实现**：\n153: ```python\n154: def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any:\n155:     original_version = metadata.version\n156:     # 递增版本号\n157:     new_version = semver.VersionInfo.parse(original_version).bump_patch()\n158:     metadata.version = str(new_version)\n159:     # 更新元数据文件\n160:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n161:     return original_version  # 返回原始版本以便回滚\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### 代理配置策略\n165: \n166: **选择**：通过 `--proxy` 参数传递代理 URL，传递给 Docker 构建参数\n167: \n168: **理由**：\n169: - 支持企业内网环境\n170: - 灵活配置代理\n171: - 避免硬编码\n172: \n173: **实现**：\n174: ```python\n175: build_args = {}\n176: if proxy:\n177:     build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = proxy\n178:     build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = proxy\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### 输出格式策略\n182: \n183: **选择**：使用 Rich 美化输出，包括构建进度和结果\n184: \n185: **理由**：\n186: - 提供良好的用户体验\n187: - 清晰展示构建状态\n188: - 支持颜色和图标\n189: \n190: **实现**：\n191: ```python\n192: from rich.console import Console\n193: from rich.progress import Progress\n194: \n195: console = Console()\n196: with Progress() as progress:\n197:     task = progress.add_task(\"Building image...\", total=100)\n198:     # 构建进度更新\n199:     progress.update(task, advance=50)\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ## Alternatives Considered\n203: \n204: ### Alternative 1: 手动指定版本号\n205: \n206: **描述**：每次构建时手动指定版本号，不自动递增\n207: \n208: **优点**：\n209: - 用户完全控制版本号\n210: - 灵活性高\n211: \n212: **缺点**：\n213: - 增加用户负担\n214: - 容易出错\n215: - 版本号冲突\n216: \n217: **选择**：不采纳 - 自动递增更方便\n218: \n219: ### Alternative 2: 不支持云端构建\n220: \n221: **描述**：仅支持本地 Docker 构建\n222: \n223: **优点**：\n224: - 实现简单\n225: - 依赖少\n226: \n227: **缺点**：\n228: - 无法满足大规模部署需求\n229: - 无法利用云服务商优势\n230: \n231: **选择**：不采纳 - 云端构建是生产环境必需\n232: \n233: ### Alternative 3: 构建失败时不回滚版本\n234: \n235: **描述**：即使构建失败，也保留递增后的版本号\n236: \n237: **优点**：\n238: - 实现简单\n239: - 避免版本号重复\n240: \n241: **缺点**：\n242: - 版本号不一致\n243: - 用户困惑\n244: \n245: **选择**：不采纳 - 回滚机制保证一致性\n246: \n247: ## Implementation Plan\n248: \n249: ### Phase 1: BuildRuntime 基础框架 (Day 1)\n250: \n251: 1. 创建 `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` 文件\n252: 2. 实现 `BuildRuntime` 类基础结构\n253: 3. 实现 `__init__` 方法\n254: 4. 实现 `build()` 方法框架\n255: \n256: **代码框架**：\n257: ```python\n258: from pathlib import Path\n259: from typing import Any, Dict\n260: import logging\n261: \n262: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n263: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n264: \n265: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n266: \n267: class BuildRuntime:\n268:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n269:         self.verbose = verbose\n270:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n271:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n272: \n273:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n274:         \"\"\"Build container image from workspace.\"\"\"\n275:         # 实现构建逻辑\n276:         pass\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ### Phase 2: 版本管理实现 (Day 1)\n280: \n281: 1. 实现 `_increment_version()` 方法\n282: 2. 实现版本号解析和递增\n283: 3. 实现版本回滚机制\n284: \n285: **实现**：\n286: ```python\n287: import semver\n288: \n289: def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any:\n290:     \"\"\"Increment version number and return original version.\"\"\"\n291:     original_version = metadata.version or \"0.0.0\"\n292:     if self.verbose:\n293:         logger.info(f\"Original version: {original_version}\")\n294: \n295:     # 解析版本号\n296:     try:\n297:         version_info = semver.VersionInfo.parse(original_version)\n298:     except ValueError:\n299:         # 如果版本号不符合语义化版本，添加 `.1` 后缀\n300:         new_version = f\"{original_version}.1\"\n301:     else:\n302:         # 递增 patch 版本\n303:         new_version = str(version_info.bump_patch())\n304: \n305:     if self.verbose:\n306:         logger.info(f\"New version: {new_version}\")\n307: \n308:     # 更新元数据\n309:     metadata.version = new_version\n310:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n311: \n312:     return original_version\n313: ```\n314: \n315: ### Phase 3: 前置条件验证 (Day 2)\n316: \n317: 1. 实现 `_validate_build_prerequisites()` 方法\n318: 2. 验证 Docker 守护进程可用性\n319: 3. 验证 Dockerfile 存在\n320: 4. 验证元数据完整性\n321: \n322: **实现**：\n323: ```python\n324: def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n325:     \"\"\"Validate build prerequisites.\"\"\"\n326:     # 验证 Docker 可用性\n327:     if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n328:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n329: \n330:     # 验证 Dockerfile 存在\n331:     dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n332:     if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n333:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Dockerfile not found: {dockerfile_path}\")\n334: \n335:     if self.verbose:\n336:         logger.info(f\"Dockerfile found: {dockerfile_path}\")\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ### Phase 4: 本地构建实现 (Day 2-3)\n340: \n341: 1. 实现 `_build_local()` 方法\n342: 2. 集成 Docker 服务\n343: 3. 支持代理配置\n344: 4. 返回构建结果\n345: \n346: **实现**：\n347: ```python\n348: def _build_local(\n349:     self,\n350:     workspace_path: Path,\n351:     metadata,\n352:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n353: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n354:     \"\"\"Build image using local Docker.\"\"\"\n355:     if self.verbose:\n356:         logger.info(\"Starting local build...\")\n357: \n358:     # 准备构建参数\n359:     build_args = {}\n360:     proxy = options.get(\"proxy\")\n361:     if proxy:\n362:         build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = proxy\n363:         build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = proxy\n364:         if self.verbose:\n365:             logger.info(f\"Using proxy: {proxy}\")\n366: \n367:     # 准备镜像名称和标签\n368:     image_name = metadata.agent_name\n369:     tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n370:     dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n371: \n372:     # 构建镜像\n373:     build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n374:         dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n375:         context_path=workspace_path,\n376:         image_name=image_name,\n377:         tag=tag,\n378:         build_args=build_args if build_args else None\n379:     )\n380: \n381:     if self.verbose:\n382:         logger.info(f\"Build completed: {build_result}\")\n383: \n384:     # 更新元数据\n385:     self._update_build_metadata(\n386:         workspace_path,\n387:         metadata,\n388:         build_result,\n389:         tag\n390:     )\n391: \n392:     return build_result\n393: ```\n394: \n395: ### Phase 5: 云端构建实现 (Day 3-4)\n396: \n397: 1. 实现 `_build_cloud()` 方法\n398: 2. 集成云服务商 SDK\n399: 3. 支持华为云等云服务\n400: 4. 返回构建结果\n401: \n402: **实现**（框架）：\n403: ```python\n404: def _build_cloud(\n405:     self,\n406:     workspace_path: Path,\n407:     metadata,\n408:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n409: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n410:     \"\"\"Build image using cloud provider.\"\"\"\n411:     cloud_provider = options.get(\"cloud_provider\", \"huawei\")\n412: \n413:     if self.verbose:\n414:         logger.info(f\"Starting cloud build with provider: {cloud_provider}\")\n415: \n416:     if cloud_provider == \"huawei\":\n417:         return self._build_huawei_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n418:     else:\n419:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported cloud provider: {cloud_provider}\")\n420: \n421: def _build_huawei_cloud(\n422:     self,\n423:     workspace_path: Path,\n424:     metadata,\n425:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n426: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n427:     \"\"\"Build image using Huawei Cloud.\"\"\"\n428:     # 实现华为云构建逻辑\n429:     # TODO: 集成华为云 SDK\n430:     pass\n431: ```\n432: \n433: ### Phase 6: 元数据更新实现 (Day 4)\n434: \n435: 1. 实现 `_update_build_metadata()` 方法\n436: 2. 更新镜像信息\n437: 3. 更新构建时间\n438: 4. 持久化元数据\n439: \n440: **实现**：\n441: ```python\n442: from datetime import datetime\n443: \n444: def _update_build_metadata(\n445:     self,\n446:     workspace_path: Path,\n447:     metadata,\n448:     build_result: Dict[str, str],\n449:     tag: str = \"latest\"\n450: ) -> None:\n451:     \"\"\"Update metadata with build information.\"\"\"\n452:     # 更新镜像信息\n453:     metadata.image = {\n454:         \"name\": build_result.get(\"image_name\"),\n455:         \"id\": build_result.get(\"image_id\"),\n456:         \"size\": build_result.get(\"image_size\"),\n457:         \"tag\": tag,\n458:         \"build_time\": build_result.get(\"build_time\") or datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n459:     }\n460: \n461:     # 保存元数据\n462:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n463: \n464:     if self.verbose:\n465:         logger.info(f\"Metadata updated: {metadata.image}\")\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ### Phase 7: CLI 命令集成 (Day 4)\n469: \n470: 1. 在 `agentcube/cli/main.py` 中添加 `build` 命令\n471: 2. 添加命令行参数\n472: 3. 集成 BuildRuntime\n473: 4. 实现错误处理\n474: \n475: **实现**：\n476: ```python\n477: import typer\n478: from pathlib import Path\n479: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n480: \n481: def build(\n482:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n483:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n484:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n485:         show_default=True\n486:     ),\n487:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n488:         None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\",\n489:         help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n490:     ),\n491:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n492:         None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n493:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n494:     ),\n495:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n496:         None, \"--output\",\n497:         help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n498:     ),\n499:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n500:         False, \"--verbose\",\n501:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"\n502:     )\n503: ) -> None:\n504:     \"\"\"Build container image from packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n505:     workspace_path = Path(workspace)\n506: \n507:     try:\n508:         runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n509:         result = runtime.build(\n510:             workspace_path=workspace_path,\n511:             proxy=proxy,\n512:             cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n513:             output=output\n514:         )\n515: \n516:         # 输出构建结果\n517:         console = Console()\n518:         console.print(\"[green]✓[/green] Build completed successfully!\")\n519:         console.print(f\"  Image: {result.get('image_name')}:{result.get('tag')}\")\n520:         console.print(f\"  ID: {result.get('image_id')}\")\n521:         console.print(f\"  Size: {result.get('image_size')}\")\n522:         console.print(f\"  Time: {result.get('build_time')}\")\n523: \n524:     except Exception as e:\n525:         _handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ### Phase 8: 错误处理和回滚 (Day 4-5)\n529: \n530: 1. 实现构建失败时的版本回滚\n531: 2. 实现详细的错误信息输出\n532: 3. 实现日志记录\n533: \n534: **实现**：\n535: ```python\n536: def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n537:     \"\"\"Build container image from workspace.\"\"\"\n538:     # 加载元数据\n539:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n540: \n541:     # 递增版本号\n542:     original_version = self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n543: \n544:     try:\n545:         # 验证前置条件\n546:         self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n547: \n548:         # 执行构建\n549:         build_mode = metadata.build_mode or \"local\"\n550:         if build_mode == \"local\":\n551:             result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n552:         elif build_mode == \"cloud\":\n553:             result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n554:         else:\n555:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {build_mode}\")\n556: \n557:         return result\n558: \n559:     except Exception as e:\n560:         # 回滚版本号\n561:         if self.verbose:\n562:             logger.warning(f\"Build failed, rolling back version to {original_version}\")\n563: \n564:         metadata.version = original_version\n565:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n566: \n567:         raise\n568: ```\n569: \n570: ### Phase 9: 测试 (Day 5-6)\n571: \n572: 1. 单元测试\n573:    - 测试版本递增逻辑\n574:    - 测试前置条件验证\n575:    - 测试本地构建\n576:    - 测试错误处理\n577: \n578: 2. 集成测试\n579:    - 测试完整的构建流程\n580:    - 测试与 Docker 集成\n581:    - 测试元数据更新\n582: \n583: 3. 端到端测试\n584:    - 测试 `pack` → `build` → `publish` 链路\n585:    - 测试构建失败回滚\n586: \n587: ### Phase 10: 文档 (Day 6)\n588: \n589: 1. 更新 CLI 文档\n590: 2. 添加使用示例\n591: 3. 添加故障排查指南\n592: 4. 更新 README\n593: \n594: ## Testing Strategy\n595: \n596: ### Unit Tests\n597: \n598: 1. **版本管理测试**\n599:    - 测试正常版本号递增\n600:    - 测试无效版本号处理\n601:    - 测试版本回滚\n602: \n603: 2. **前置条件验证测试**\n604:    - 测试 Docker 可用性检查\n605:    - 测试 Dockerfile 存在检查\n606:    - 测试元数据完整性检查\n607: \n608: 3. **本地构建测试**\n609:    - 测试成功构建\n610:    - 测试代理配置\n611:    - 测试构建失败\n612: \n613: 4. **错误处理测试**\n614:    - 测试版本回滚\n615:    - 测试错误信息输出\n616:    - 测试日志记录\n617: \n618: ### Integration Tests\n619: \n620: 1. **Docker 集成测试**\n621:    - 测试真实 Docker 构建\n622:    - 测试构建参数传递\n623:    - 测试构建结果解析\n624: \n625: 2. **元数据集成测试**\n626:    - 测试元数据加载\n627:    - 测试元数据更新\n628:    - 测试元数据持久化\n629: \n630: 3. **完整流程测试**\n631:    - 测试 `pack` → `build` 链路\n632:    - 测试 `build` → `publish` 链路\n633:    - 测试完整生命周期\n634: \n635: ### Test Coverage\n636: \n637: 目标：> 80% 代码覆盖率\n638: \n639: ## Configuration\n640: \n641: ### 命令行参数\n642: \n643: | 参数 | 类型 | 默认值 | 说明 |\n644: |------|------|--------|------|\n645: | `--workspace` / `-f` | str | `\".\"` | 工作空间路径 |\n646: | `--proxy` / `-p` | str | `None` | 代理 URL |\n647: | `--cloud-provider` | str | `None` | 云服务提供商 |\n648: | `--output` | str | `None` | 输出路径 |\n649: | `--verbose` | bool | `False` | 详细日志 |\n650: \n651: ### 元数据配置\n652: \n653: 在 `agent_metadata.yaml` 中：\n654: \n655: ```yaml\n656: agent_name: \"my-agent\"\n657: version: \"0.1.0\"\n658: build_mode: \"local\"  # 或 \"cloud\"\n659: ```\n660: \n661: ### 环境变量\n662: \n663: | 变量 | 说明 |\n664: |------|------|\n665: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker 守护进程地址 |\n666: | `HTTP_PROXY` | HTTP 代理 |\n667: | `HTTPS_PROXY` | HTTPS 代理 |\n668: | `NO_PROXY` | 不使用代理的主机 |\n669: \n670: ## API Specification\n671: \n672: ### build() 方法签名\n673: \n674: ```python\n675: def build(\n676:     workspace_path: Path,\n677:     proxy: Optional[str] = None,\n678:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None,\n679:     output: Optional[str] = None,\n680:     verbose: bool = False\n681: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n682: ```\n683: \n684: ### 返回值\n685: \n686: ```python\n687: {\n688:     \"image_name\": \"my-agent\",\n689:     \"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n690:     \"image_size\": \"150MB\",\n691:     \"tag\": \"0.1.1\",\n692:     \"build_time\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n693: }\n694: ```\n695: \n696: ### 异常\n697: \n698: - `RuntimeError` - Docker 不可用\n699: - `FileNotFoundError` - Dockerfile 不存在\n700: - `ValueError` - 无效的构建模式或云服务提供商\n701: - `Exception` - 其他构建错误\n702: \n703: ## Security Considerations\n704: \n705: 1. **Docker 守护进程安全**\n706:    - 验证 Docker 守护进程连接\n707:    - 避免构建特权容器\n708:    - 限制 Docker 访问权限\n709: \n710: 2. **代理安全**\n711:    - 支持安全代理（HTTPS）\n712:    - 避免在日志中输出代理凭证\n713:    - 支持环境变量配置\n714: \n715: 3. **元数据安全**\n716:    - 避免在元数据中存储敏感信息\n717:    - 确保文件权限正确\n718:    - 支持元数据加密（可选）\n719: \n720: 4. **云构建安全**\n721:    - 支持云服务认证\n722:    - 避免硬编码凭证\n723:    - 支持凭证轮换\n724: \n725: ## Performance Considerations\n726: \n727: 1. **构建性能**\n728:    - 利用 Docker 缓存层\n729:    - 支持并行构建（可选）\n730:    - 优化 Dockerfile 指令顺序\n731: \n732: 2. **资源使用**\n733:    - 控制构建内存使用\n734:    - 限制构建并发数\n735:    - 支持构建超时\n736: \n737: 3. **网络性能**\n738:    - 支持代理加速\n739:    - 支持镜像缓存\n740:    - 优化依赖下载\n741: \n742: ## Monitoring and Metrics\n743: \n744: ### 日志记录\n745: \n746: 使用 Python 标准库 `logging`：\n747: \n748: - 构建开始/结束\n749: - 版本变更\n750: - 错误信息\n751: - 调试信息（verbose 模式）\n752: \n753: ### 构建指标\n754: \n755: - 构建时间\n756: - 镜像大小\n757: - 构建成功率\n758: - 构建失败原因\n759: \n760: ## Open Questions\n761: \n762: 1. **Q1**: 是否需要支持多架构构建？\n763:    - **当前**: 不支持\n764:    - **讨论**: 支持 AMD64、ARM64 等多架构\n765:    - **决策**: 初始不支持，后续根据需求添加\n766: \n767: 2. **Q2**: 云端构建是否需要支持多个云服务商？\n768:    - **当前**: 仅支持华为云\n769:    - **讨论**: 支持阿里云、AWS 等\n770:    - **决策**: 初始仅支持华为云，后续扩展\n771: \n772: 3. **Q3**: 是否需要支持构建缓存？\n773:    - **当前**: 使用 Docker 默认缓存\n774:    - **讨论**: 自定义缓存策略\n775:    - **决策**: 初始使用 Docker 缓存，后续优化\n776: \n777: 4. **Q4**: 是否需要支持构建进度通知？\n778:    - **当前**: 仅日志输出\n779:    - **讨论**: Webhook、邮件通知等\n780:    - **决策**: 初始不支持，后续根据需求添加\n781: \n782: ## Next Steps\n783: \n784: 1. 创建 BuildRuntime 类\n785: 2. 实现版本管理功能\n786: 3. 实现本地 Docker 构建\n787: 4. 实现 CLI 命令集成\n788: 5. 编写单元测试和集成测试\n789: 6. 更新文档\n790: 7. 集成到 CI/CD 流程\n791: \n792: ## References\n793: \n794: - [AgentCube CLI Design](../cli-toolkit/design.md)\n795: - [AgentCube CLI Spec](../cli-toolkit/spec.md)\n796: - [Docker SDK for Python](https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/)\n797: - [SemVer](https://semver.org/)\n798: - [Typer Documentation](https://typer.tiangolo.com/)\n\n(End of file - total 798 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021: CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n实现 AgentCube CLI 的 `build` 命令，用于从打包好的工作空间构建容器镜像。该命令支持本地 Docker 构建和云端构建两种模式，能够自动管理版本号、验证构建前置条件，并集成 Docker 服务进行镜像构建。\n\n## Purpose\n\n提供 `kubectl-agentcube build` 命令，实现：\n\n1. **本地 Docker 构建**：使用本地 Docker 守护进程构建容器镜像\n2. **云端构建**：集成云服务商（如华为云）的构建服务\n3. **版本管理**：自动递增版本号（patch 级别），构建失败时回滚版本\n4. **代理支持**：支持自定义代理 URL 进行依赖解析\n5. **构建结果输出**：输出镜像名称、ID、大小等构建信息\n6. **元数据更新**：更新 `agent_metadata.yaml` 中的构建信息\n\n## Module\n\n`cmd/cli` - AgentCube CLI 工具包","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775867132975,"end":1775867132993}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867133000,"sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","part":{"id":"prt_d79edf41b0014wzpHGsQhN3cSS","messageID":"msg_d79ede6f1001AoyYf2GUcODcCA","sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-801d0eec9b59441ebcfa679a4bf9b0d0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/tasks-AR-021.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/tasks-AR-021.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Tasks for AR-021: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: **Module**: cmd/cli\n4: **Language**: Python\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Status**: Implementation Complete, Tests Pending\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: The `build` command is already implemented in `build_runtime.py` and integrated in `main.py`. All core functionality is working, but comprehensive test coverage is missing. This checklist focuses on adding test coverage following TDD principles.\n11: \n12: ## Implementation Status\n13: \n14: - ✅ `build_runtime.py` - Complete\n15: - ✅ `docker_service.py` - Complete  \n16: - ✅ CLI integration in `main.py` - Complete\n17: - ❌ Test coverage for `build_runtime.py` - Missing\n18: - ❌ Test coverage for `docker_service.py` - Missing\n19: - ❌ Integration tests - Missing\n20: \n21: ## Test Tasks\n22: \n23: ### Unit Tests for BuildRuntime\n24: \n25: - [ ] **T-001**: Create `test_build_runtime.py` file structure\n26:   - Create test file: `tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n27:   - Add TestBuildRuntime class\n28:   - Configure pytest fixtures for workspace setup\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T-002**: Test `_increment_version()` - Semantic version patch increment\n31:   - Input: version=\"1.0.0\"\n32:   - Expected output: version=\"1.0.1\"\n33:   - Verify metadata is updated and saved\n34: \n35: - [ ] **T-003**: Test `_increment_version()` - Prerelease version increment\n36:   - Input: version=\"1.0.0-alpha.1\"\n37:   - Expected output: version=\"1.0.0-alpha.2\"\n38:   - Verify prerelease number increments correctly\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T-004**: Test `_increment_version()` - Custom version with suffix\n41:   - Input: version=\"custom-version\"\n42:   - Expected output: version=\"custom-version-1\"\n43:   - Verify non-semantic version handling\n44: \n45: - [ ] **T-005**: Test `_increment_version()` - No version (default to 0.1.0)\n46:   - Input: version=None\n47:   - Expected output: version=\"0.1.0\"\n48:   - Verify default version assignment\n49: \n50: - [ ] **T-006**: Test `_validate_build_prerequisites()` - Missing Dockerfile\n51:   - Setup: workspace without Dockerfile\n52:   - Expected: raises ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found\")\n53:   - Verify error message matches expected\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T-007**: Test `_validate_build_prerequisites()` - Docker unavailable\n56:   - Setup: workspace with Dockerfile, mock DockerService.check_docker_available()=False\n57:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available\")\n58:   - Verify Docker availability check\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T-008**: Test `_validate_build_prerequisites()` - Valid workspace\n61:   - Setup: workspace with Dockerfile, mock DockerService.check_docker_available()=True\n62:   - Expected: no exception raised\n63:   - Verify validation passes\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T-009**: Test `_build_local()` - Basic local build\n66:   - Setup: workspace with Dockerfile and metadata\n67:   - Mock: DockerService.build_image() returns build result\n68:   - Expected: result contains image_name with correct tag\n69:   - Verify build_image called with correct parameters\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T-010**: Test `_build_local()` - Build with proxy\n72:   - Setup: workspace with Dockerfile and metadata\n73:   - Options: proxy=\"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"\n74:   - Expected: build_args contains HTTP_PROXY and HTTPS_PROXY\n75:   - Verify proxy arguments passed to Docker build\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T-011**: Test `_build_cloud()` - Cloud build with provider\n78:   - Setup: workspace with metadata\n79:   - Options: cloud_provider=\"huawei\"\n80:   - Expected: result contains cloud provider prefix in image_name\n81:   - Verify cloud provider name logged\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T-012**: Test `_build_cloud()` - Default cloud provider\n84:   - Setup: workspace with metadata\n85:   - Options: no cloud_provider specified\n86:   - Expected: uses \"huawei\" as default provider\n87:   - Verify default provider handling\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T-013**: Test `_update_build_metadata()` - Update with build result\n90:   - Setup: workspace with metadata, build_result dict\n91:   - Expected: metadata.image field updated with build result\n92:   - Verify metadata saved to file\n93: \n94: - [ ] **T-014**: Test `_update_build_metadata()` - Merge with existing image data\n95:   - Setup: workspace with metadata containing existing image data\n96:   - Expected: new build result merged with existing data\n97:   - Verify merge behavior\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T-015**: Test `build()` - Successful local build\n100:   - Setup: complete workspace with Dockerfile, metadata\n101:   - Mock: all dependencies return success\n102:   - Expected: returns BuildResult dict with all fields\n103:   - Verify version incremented and metadata updated\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T-016**: Test `build()` - Version reversion on build failure\n106:   - Setup: workspace with version=\"1.0.0\"\n107:   - Mock: _build_local() raises RuntimeError\n108:   - Expected: version reverted to \"1.0.0\"\n109:   - Verify metadata saved with reverted version\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T-017**: Test `build()` - Cloud build mode\n112:   - Setup: workspace with build_mode=\"cloud\"\n113:   - Expected: calls _build_cloud() instead of _build_local()\n114:   - Verify build mode selection logic\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T-018**: Test `build()` - Missing metadata file\n117:   - Setup: workspace without metadata file\n118:   - Expected: raises FileNotFoundError\n119:   - Verify error handling for missing metadata\n120: \n121: - [ ] **T-019**: Test `build()` - Invalid build mode in metadata\n122:   - Setup: metadata with build_mode=\"invalid\"\n123:   - Expected: raises ValueError or handles gracefully\n124:   - Verify build mode validation\n125: \n126: ### Unit Tests for DockerService\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T-020**: Create `test_docker_service.py` file structure\n129:   - Create test file: `tests/test_docker_service.py`\n130:   - Add TestDockerService class\n131:   - Configure pytest fixtures for Docker mocking\n132: \n133: - [ ] **T-021**: Test `check_docker_available()` - Docker available\n134:   - Mock: docker.from_env().ping() returns success\n135:   - Expected: returns True\n136:   - Verify Docker availability check\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T-022**: Test `check_docker_available()` - Docker unavailable\n139:   - Mock: docker.from_env().ping() raises DockerException\n140:   - Expected: returns False\n141:   - Verify error handling and logging\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T-023**: Test `build_image()` - Successful build\n144:   - Setup: valid dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name\n145:   - Mock: client.images.build() returns image and logs\n146:   - Expected: returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n147:   - Verify build parameters passed correctly\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T-024**: Test `build_image()` - Build with custom tag\n150:   - Setup: tag=\"v1.0.0\"\n151:   - Expected: image built with correct tag\n152:   - Verify tag format in full_image_name\n153: \n154: - [ ] **T-025**: Test `build_image()` - Build with build arguments\n155:   - Setup: build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy\"}\n156:   - Expected: build args passed to Docker build\n157:   - Verify build arguments handling\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T-026**: Test `build_image()` - Docker unavailable\n160:   - Mock: check_docker_available() returns False\n161:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available\")\n162:   - Verify prerequisite check\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T-027**: Test `build_image()` - Docker build failure\n165:   - Mock: client.images.build() raises DockerException\n166:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError with original exception\n167:   - Verify error propagation\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T-028**: Test `get_image_info()` - Get existing image info\n170:   - Mock: client.images.get() returns image with attrs\n171:   - Expected: returns dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, size_bytes\n172:   - Verify image ID truncated to 12 chars\n173:   - Verify size formatting\n174: \n175: - [ ] **T-029**: Test `get_image_info()` - Image not found\n176:   - Mock: client.images.get() raises DockerException\n177:   - Expected: returns empty dict (logged as warning)\n178:   - Verify graceful degradation\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T-030**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in bytes\n181:   - Input: 512\n182:   - Expected: \"512.00 B\"\n183:   - Verify size formatting for bytes\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T-031**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in KB\n186:   - Input: 2048\n187:   - Expected: \"2.00 KB\"\n188:   - Verify size formatting for KB\n189: \n190: - [ ] **T-032**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in MB\n191:   - Input: 1048576\n192:   - Expected: \"1.00 MB\"\n193:   - Verify size formatting for MB\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T-033**: Test `_format_size()` - Size in GB\n196:   - Input: 1073741824\n197:   - Expected: \"1.00 GB\"\n198:   - Verify size formatting for GB\n199: \n200: - [ ] **T-034**: Test `push_image()` - Push to default registry\n201:   - Setup: image_name without registry prefix\n202:   - Mock: client.images.push() returns success logs\n203:   - Expected: returns dict with pushed_image and push_time\n204:   - Verify push to default registry\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T-035**: Test `push_image()` - Push to custom registry\n207:   - Setup: registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"\n208:   - Mock: _tag_image_sdk() and client.images.push()\n209:   - Expected: image tagged and pushed to custom registry\n210:   - Verify registry URL handling\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T-036**: Test `push_image()` - Push with authentication\n213:   - Setup: username and password provided\n214:   - Mock: _docker_login_sdk() and client.images.push()\n215:   - Expected: login performed before push\n216:   - Verify authentication flow\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T-037**: Test `push_image()` - Push failure\n219:   - Mock: client.images.push() returns error in logs\n220:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError with error message\n221:   - Verify error handling for push failures\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T-038**: Test `_docker_login_sdk()` - Successful login\n224:   - Mock: client.login() returns success\n225:   - Expected: login called with correct credentials\n226:   - Verify login parameters\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T-039**: Test `_docker_login_sdk()` - Login failure\n229:   - Mock: client.login() raises DockerException\n230:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError with original exception\n231:   - Verify error propagation\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T-040**: Test `_tag_image_sdk()` - Successful tagging\n234:   - Mock: client.images.get() and image.tag()\n235:   - Expected: image tagged with force=True\n236:   - Verify tagging parameters\n237: \n238: - [ ] **T-041**: Test `_tag_image_sdk()` - Tag failure\n239:   - Mock: client.images.get() raises DockerException\n240:   - Expected: raises RuntimeError with original exception\n241:   - Verify error handling\n242: \n243: - [ ] **T-042**: Test `remove_image()` - Successful removal\n244:   - Mock: client.images.remove() returns success\n245:   - Expected: returns True\n246:   - Verify removal called with force=True\n247: \n248: - [ ] **T-043**: Test `remove_image()` - Removal failure\n249:   - Mock: client.images.remove() raises DockerException\n250:   - Expected: returns False (logged as warning)\n251:   - Verify graceful degradation\n252: \n253: ### Integration Tests\n254: \n255: - [ ] **T-044**: Test end-to-end local build with Docker\n256:   - Setup: complete workspace with valid Dockerfile\n257:   - Mock: real Docker operations (or use test Docker daemon)\n258:   - Expected: successful build with valid image\n259:   - Verify: image created, metadata updated, version incremented\n260: \n261: - [ ] **T-045**: Test build with proxy in real environment\n262:   - Setup: workspace requiring proxy for dependencies\n263:   - Expected: build succeeds with proxy configuration\n264:   - Verify proxy build args used\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T-046**: Test build failure and recovery\n267:   - Setup: workspace with invalid Dockerfile\n268:   - Expected: build fails, version reverted\n269:   - Verify error handling and rollback\n270: \n271: - [ ] **T-047**: Test multiple sequential builds\n272:   - Setup: workspace, run build twice\n273:   - Expected: version increments correctly each time\n274:   - Verify version management across builds\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T-048**: Test build with different metadata versions\n277:   - Setup: workspace with various version formats\n278:   - Expected: each version format handled correctly\n279:   - Verify version increment rules\n280: \n281: ### Test Infrastructure\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T-049**: Add pytest fixtures for workspace setup\n284:   - Create fixtures for temporary workspaces\n285:   - Create fixtures for mock DockerService\n286:   - Create fixtures for mock MetadataService\n287:   - Ensure fixtures are reusable across tests\n288: \n289: - [ ] **T-050**: Configure test coverage reporting\n290:   - Add pytest-cov configuration\n291:   - Set coverage targets: build_runtime.py 90%+, docker_service.py 85%+\n292:   - Add coverage reporting to CI/CD pipeline\n293: \n294: - [ ] **T-051**: Add integration test markers\n295:   - Add pytest marker for integration tests\n296:   - Configure pytest to skip integration tests by default\n297:   - Add documentation for running integration tests\n298: \n299: - [ ] **T-052**: Add test data fixtures\n300:   - Create sample Dockerfiles for testing\n301:   - Create sample metadata files for testing\n302:   - Create sample workspace structures\n303: \n304: ### Code Quality\n305: \n306: - [ ] **T-053**: Run linter on test files\n307:   - Run `ruff check tests/`\n308:   - Fix any linting issues\n309:   - Ensure code follows project style guidelines\n310: \n311: - [ ] **T-054**: Run type checker on test files\n312:   - Run `mypy tests/`\n313:   - Fix any type checking issues\n314:   - Ensure type hints are correct\n315: \n316: - [ ] **T-055**: Verify test documentation\n317:   - Add docstrings to all test classes and methods\n318:   - Document test purpose and expected behavior\n319:   - Ensure test names are descriptive\n320: \n321: ### Verification Tasks\n322: \n323: - [ ] **T-056**: Run all tests and ensure 100% pass rate\n324:   - Run `pytest tests/`\n325:   - Verify all tests pass\n326:   - Review any failures and fix\n327: \n328: - [ ] **T-057**: Generate coverage report\n329:   - Run `pytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.build_runtime --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service`\n330:   - Verify coverage meets targets\n331:   - Add coverage badge if below target\n332: \n333: - [ ] **T-058**: Manual testing of build command\n334:   - Test `kubectl-agentcube build` with real workspace\n335:   - Test with proxy option\n336:   - Test with verbose option\n337:   - Verify error handling\n338: \n339: - [ ] **T-059**: Test error messages\n340:   - Test all error scenarios manually\n341:   - Verify error messages are user-friendly\n342:   - Verify error messages match design specifications\n343: \n344: - [ ] **T-060**: Document test execution\n345:   - Add test execution instructions to README\n346:   - Document how to run unit vs integration tests\n347:   - Document test prerequisites (Docker daemon)\n348: \n349: ## Task Dependencies\n350: \n351: - T-001 must be completed before T-002 through T-019\n352: - T-020 must be completed before T-021 through T-043\n353: - T-049 should be completed early to support other test tasks\n354: - T-044 through T-048 require Docker daemon and should be marked