{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867191750,"sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","part":{"id":"prt_d79eee199001EOqYActzrfoiz4","messageID":"msg_d79eed529001jfA3mZTpz8F25b","sessionID":"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b8b1b01a498b4f0b80aefef0f1465a41","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\n10: \n11: The system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\n12: \n13: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n14: - Command name: `build`\n15: - Supports workspace path specification\n16: - Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\n17: - Supports cloud provider selection\n18: - Supports custom output path for build artifacts\n19: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n20: \n21: **Scenarios:**\n22: \n23: #### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\n24: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n25: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` without options\n26: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n27:   - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n28:   - `proxy`: `None`\n29:   - `cloud_provider`: `None`\n30:   - `output`: `None`\n31:   - `verbose`: `False`\n32: \n33: #### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\n34: - **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\n35: - **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\n37:   - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\n38:   - `proxy`: string URL or None\n39:   - `cloud_provider`: string provider name or None\n40:   - `output`: string path or None\n41:   - `verbose`: boolean flag\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Build metadata validation\n46: \n47: The system SHALL validate that required metadata fields exist before attempting to build the container image.\n48: \n49: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n50: - Validates metadata file existence\n51: - Validates required metadata fields\n52: - Validates metadata field values\n53: - Provides clear error messages for validation failures\n54: \n55: **Scenarios:**\n56: \n57: #### Scenario 2.1: Missing metadata file\n58: - **GIVEN** the workspace path exists but has no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n59: - **WHEN** the `build` command is executed\n60: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n61:   - Raise `ValueError` with message indicating metadata file not found\n62:   - Exit with code `1`\n63: \n64: #### Scenario 2.2: Missing required fields in metadata\n65: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields (`agent_name`, `entrypoint`, `language`)\n66: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n67: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n68:   - Raise `ValueError` specifying which required fields are missing\n69:   - Exit with code `1`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario 2.3: Invalid build_mode in metadata\n72: - **GIVEN** the metadata contains `build_mode` not equal to `local` or `cloud`\n73: - **WHEN** the build command is executed\n74: - **THEN** Pydantic validator SHALL:\n75:   - Reject the metadata with validation error\n76:   - Display error message about valid build_mode values\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Local Docker build prerequisites\n81: \n82: The system SHALL validate Docker availability and configuration before attempting local builds.\n83: \n84: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n85: - Checks Docker daemon availability\n86: - Validates Docker daemon is running\n87: - Provides clear error messages when Docker is unavailable\n88: \n89: **Scenarios:**\n90: \n91: #### Scenario 3.1: Docker daemon not available\n92: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not installed or not running\n93: - **WHEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local` and `DockerService.check_docker_available` returns `False`\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n95:   - Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n96:   - Surface error via CLI error handling\n97:   - Exit with code `1`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario 3.2: Docker daemon available\n100: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 919. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Command name: `build`\n- Supports workspace path specification\n- Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\n- Supports cloud provider selection\n- Supports custom output path for build artifacts\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867191738,"end":1775867191748}}}}
